r films, writers and collaborators. It should be essential reading for students and academics studying Fellini’s work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBondanella, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuzzati, Dino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFellini, Federico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRondi, Brunello, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZapponi, Bernardino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745971840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857459718423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857459718/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK